M|references|Detailed formulas and templates for writing high-converting ad copy.
M|references|- Primary Text Formulas (Problem-Agitate-Solve, Before-After-Bridge, soc Proof Lead, Feature-Benefit Bridge, Direct rsp)
M|references|- Headline Formulas (For Search Ads, For soc Ads)
M|references|- CTA Variations (Soft CTAs, Hard CTAs, Urgency CTAs, Action-Oriented CTAs)
M|references|- Platform-Specific Copy Guidelines (Google Search Ads, Meta Ads, LinkedIn Ads)
M|references|- Copy Testing Priority
M|references|```
M|references|[Problem statement]
M|references|[Agitate the pain]
M|references|[Introduce solution]
M|references|[CTA]
M|references|```
M|references|**Example:**
M|references|> Spending hours on manual reporting every week?
M|references|> While you're buried in spreadsheets, your cp are making decisions.
M|references|> [Product] automates your reports in minutes.
M|references|> Start your free trial →
M|references|```
M|references|[Current painful state]
M|references|[Desired future state]
M|references|[Your product as the bridge]
M|references|```
M|references|**Example:**
M|references|> Before: Chasing down approvals across email, Slack, and spreadsheets.
M|references|> After: Every ap tracked, automated, and on time.
M|references|> [Product] connects your tools and keeps projects moving.
M|references|```
M|references|[Impressive stat or testimonial]
M|references|[What you do]
M|references|[CTA]
M|references|```
M|references|**Example:**
M|references|> "We cut our reporting time by 75%." — Sarah K., mkt Director
M|references|> [Product] automates the reports you hate building.
M|references|> See how it works →
M|references|```
M|references|[Feature]
M|references|[So that...]
M|references|[Which means...]
M|references|```
M|references|**Example:**
M|references|> Real-time collaboration on documents
M|references|> So your team always works from the latest version
M|references|> Which means no more version confusion or lost work
M|references|```
M|references|[Bold claim/outcome]
M|references|[Proof point]
M|references|[CTA with urgency if genuine]
M|references|```
M|references|**Example:**
M|references|> Cut your reporting time by 80%
M|references|> Join 5,000+ mkt teams already using [Product]
M|references|> Start free → First month 50% off
M|references|| Formula | Example |
M|references||---------|---------|
M|references|| [Keyword] + [Benefit] | "Project Management That Teams Actually Use" |
M|references|| [Action] + [Outcome] | "Automate Reports \| Save 10 Hours Weekly" |
M|references|| [Question] | "Tired of Manual Data Entry?" |
M|references|| [Number] + [Benefit] | "500+ Teams Trust [Product] for [Outcome]" |
M|references|| [Keyword] + [Differentiator] | "CRM Built for Small Teams" |
M|references|| [Price/Offer] + [Keyword] | "Free Project Management \| No Credit Card" |
M|references|| Type | Example |
M|references||------|---------|
M|references|| Outcome hook | "How we 3x'd our conversion rate" |
M|references|| Curiosity hook | "The reporting hack no one talks about" |
M|references|| Contrarian hook | "Why we stopped using [common tool]" |
M|references|| Specificity hook | "The exact template we use for..." |
M|references|| Question hook | "What if you could cut your admin time in half?" |
M|references|| Number hook | "7 ways to improve your workflow today" |
M|references|| Story hook | "We almost gave up. Then we found..." |
M|references|Best for: Top of funnel, cold audiences, complex products
M|references|- Learn More
M|references|- See How It Works
M|references|- Watch Demo
M|references|- Get the Guide
M|references|- Explore Features
M|references|- See Examples
M|references|- Read the Case Study
M|references|Best for: Bottom of funnel, warm audiences, clear offers
M|references|- Start Free Trial
M|references|- Get Started Free
M|references|- Book a Demo
M|references|- Claim Your Discount
M|references|- Buy Now
M|references|- Sign Up Free
M|references|- Get Instant Access
M|references|Best for: Limited-time offers, scarcity situations
M|references|- Limited Time: 30% Off
M|references|- Offer Ends [Date]
M|references|- Only X Spots Left
M|references|- Last Chance
M|references|- Early Bird Pricing Ends Soon
M|references|Best for: Active voice, clear next step
M|references|- Start Saving Time Today
M|references|- Get Your Free Report
M|references|- See Your Score
M|references|- Calculate Your ROI
M|references|- Build Your First Project
M|references|- **Headline limits:** 30 characters each (up to 15 headlines)
M|references|- **Description limits:** 90 characters each (up to 4 descriptions)
M|references|- Include keywords naturally
M|references|- Use all available headline slots
M|references|- Include numbers and stats when possible
M|references|- Test dynamic keyword insertion
M|references|- **Primary text:** 125 characters visible (can be longer, gets truncated)
M|references|- **Headline:** 40 characters recommended
M|references|- Front-load the hook (first line matters most)
M|references|- Emojis can work but test
M|references|- Questions perform well
M|references|- Keep image text under 20%
M|references|- **Intro text:** 600 characters max (150 recommended)
M|references|- **Headline:** 200 characters max (70 recommended)
M|references|- Professional tone (but not boring)
M|references|- Specific job outcomes resonate
M|references|- Stats and soc proof important
M|references|- Avoid consumer-style hype
M|references|When testing ad copy, focus on these elements in order of impact:
M|references|1. **Hook/angle** (biggest impact on performance)
M|references|2. **Headline**
M|references|3. **Primary benefit**
M|references|4. **CTA**
M|references|5. **Supporting proof points**
M|references|Test one element at a time for clean data.